MatterName: Fines for parked or unattended semi-trailers (S.61, A.26).
MatterTitle: State Legislation Resolution requesting the New York State Legislature to pass bills introduced by Senator Padavan, S.61, and Assembly Member Clark, A.26, “AN ACT to amend the vehicle and traffic law, in relation to a fine for parked or unattended semitrailers or trailers on streets of a city with a population of one million or more”.
MatterBodyName: Committee on State and Federal Legislation

MatterName: Vacant lots in certain cities (S.62, A.28).
MatterTitle: State Legislation Resolution requesting the New York State Legislature to pass bills introduced by Senator Padavan, S.62, and Assembly Member Clark, A.28, “AN ACT to amend the general city law, in relation to vacant lots in certain cities”.
MatterBodyName: Committee on State and Federal Legislation

MatterName: Sanctions on architects, licensed engineers (A.32).
MatterTitle: State Legislation Resolution requesting the New York State Legislature to pass a bill introduced by Assembly Member Clark, A.32, “AN ACT to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to imposing administrative sanctions on registered architects, licensed professional engineers and other persons for misconduct with respect to applications and other accompanying documents submitted to the department of buildings of the city of New York”.
MatterBodyName: Committee on State and Federal Legislation

MatterName: Repeal of section 1127 (A.1501).
MatterTitle: State Legislation Resolution requesting the New York State Legislature to pass a bill introduced by Assembly Member Thiele, A.1501, “AN ACT to repeal section 1127 of the New York city charter relating to a condition precedent to employment and providing for the refund of excess payments collected after the repeal of the city earnings tax on nonresidents resulting from the application of this repealed section”.
MatterBodyName: Committee on State and Federal Legislation

MatterName: Rents and rental agreements in certain retail commercial spaces (S.1747).
MatterTitle: State Legislation Resolution requesting the New York State Legislature to pass a bill introduced by Senator Sabini, S.1747, “AN ACT in relation to the control and stabilization of rents and rental agreements in certain retail commercial spaces in cities having a population of more than one million”.
MatterBodyName: Committee on State and Federal Legislation

MatterName: Escrow accounts to protect neighboring land owners and tenants (S.1051, A.2665).
MatterTitle: State Legislation Resolution requesting the New York State Legislature to pass bills introduced by Senator Padavan, S.1051, and Assembly Member Lentol, A.2665, “AN ACT to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to establishing escrow accounts to protect neighboring landowners and tenants from damage due to construction”.
MatterBodyName: Committee on State and Federal Legislation

MatterName: Adult commercial establishments (S.308).
MatterTitle: State Legislation Resolution requesting the New York State Legislature to pass a bill introduced by Senator Maltese, S.308, “AN ACT to amend the general business law, in relation to adult commercial establishments in cities with a population of one million or more”.
MatterBodyName: Committee on State and Federal Legislation

MatterName: Eight member task force for destruction and demolition (S.1329, A.2886).
MatterTitle: State Legislation Resolution requesting the New York State Legislature to pass bills introduced by Senator Maltese, S.1329, and Assembly Member Lentol, A.2886, “AN ACT to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to creating an eight-member task force to review and approve the destruction or demolition of buildings located within the city”.
MatterBodyName: Committee on State and Federal Legislation

MatterName: Deputy sheriffs members of NYERS (S.810, A.1528).
MatterTitle: State Legislation Resolution requesting the New York State Legislature to pass bills introduced by Senator Maltese, S.810, and Assembly Member Abbate, A.1528, “AN ACT to amend the retirement and social security law, in relation to deputy sheriffs members of the New York city employees’ retirement system”.
MatterBodyName: Committee on State and Federal Legislation

MatterName: Twenty year retirement program for corrections' members below the rank of captain (S.1604, A.3209).
MatterTitle: State Legislation Resolution requesting the New York State Legislature to pass bills introduced by Senator Maltese, S.1604, and Assembly Member Diaz, A.3209, “AN ACT to amend the retirement and social security law, in relation to the twenty-year retirement program for New York city correction members below the rank of captain”.
MatterBodyName: Committee on State and Federal Legislation

MatterName: Special accidental death benefit to deputy sheriff members of NYERS (S.811, A.1527).
MatterTitle: State Legislation Resolution requesting the New York State Legislature to pass bills introduced by Senator Maltese, S.811, and Assembly Member Abbate, A.1527, “AN ACT to amend the general municipal law, in relation to providing a special accidental death benefit to deputy sheriff members of the New York city employees’ retirement system”.
MatterBodyName: Committee on State and Federal Legislation

MatterName: Clearly marking pedestrian crosswalks with city population of 1 million or more (A.1029).
MatterTitle: State Legislation Resolution requesting the New York State Legislature to pass a bill introduced by Assembly Member Dinowitz, A.1029, “AN ACT to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to clearly marking pedestrian crosswalks in any city having a population of one million or more persons”.
MatterBodyName: Committee on State and Federal Legislation

MatterName: Citizens issue parking tickets of designated officers and appointed employees of PVB (A.1006).
MatterTitle: State Legislation Resolution requesting the New York State Legislature to pass a bill introduced by Assembly Member Dinowitz, A.1006, “AN ACT to amend the administrative code of the city of New York and the vehicle and traffic law, in relation to allowing citizens to issue tickets to designated officers and appointed employees of the parking violations bureau”.
MatterBodyName: Committee on State and Federal Legislation

MatterName: Dedicate Jerome Park Reservoir tract in the bronx as parkland (A.3078).
MatterTitle: State Legislation Resolution requesting the New York State Legislature to pass a bill introduced by Assembly Member Dinowitz, A.3078, “AN ACT to dedicate Jerome Park Reservoir tract in the Bronx as parkland”.
MatterBodyName: Committee on State and Federal Legislation

MatterName: Adjudication of traffic infractions arising out of the operation of a bicycle (S.2522, A.212).
MatterTitle: State Legislation Resolution requesting the New York State Legislature to pass bills introduced by Senator Kruger, S.2522, and Assembly Member Greene, A.212, “AN ACT to amend the vehicle and traffic law and the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to the adjudication of traffic infractions arising out of the operation of a bicycle”.
MatterBodyName: Committee on State and Federal Legislation

MatterName: Registration of property and designation of mailing address (S.1490, A.1985).
MatterTitle: State Legislation Resolution requesting the New York State Legislature to pass bills introduced by Senator Dilan, S.1490, and Assembly Member Robinson, A.1985, “AN ACT to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to the registration of property and designation of mailing address”.
MatterBodyName: Committee on State and Federal Legislation

Amend the NYS Real Property Tax Law (RPTL) to expand the veterans’ property tax exemption to include an exemption on the school portion of the tax for veterans with incomes below $47,
	500.
MatterTitle:
Resolution calling upon the New York State Legislature to introduce and adopt,
	 and the Governor to sign,
	 legislation which would amend the New York State Real Property Tax Law (RPTL) to expand the veterans’ property tax exemption to include an exemption on the school portion of the tax for veterans with incomes below $47,
	500 and to increase the maximum income eligibility thresholds of the Senior Citizen Homeowners Exemption (SCHE) program and the Disabled Homeowners Exemption (DHE) program to the same level.

MatterName: NYC Economic Development Corporation to allow the historic Brooklyn Container Port to continue to operate on the Red Hook waterfront.
MatterTitle: Resolution calling upon the State of New York and the Port Authority of New York and New Jersey to allow the historic Brooklyn Container Port to continue to operate on the Red Hook waterfront and further urging that no land use policies be implemented which would have the effect of precluding the historic Brooklyn Container Port’s continued operation and valuable service to New York City and State.

MatterName: Calling on US corporate sponsors of the 2008 Beijing Summer Olympics with headquarters and operations in NYC to meaningfully engage the Chinese government in proactively addressing their role in the ongoing crisis in Darfur.
MatterTitle:
Resolution calling on United States corporate sponsors of the 2008 Beijing Summer Olympics with headquarters and operations in New York City to meaningfully engage the Chinese government in proactively addressing their role in the ongoing crisis in Darfur and to withdraw from and withhold any commitment to support the Olympics if the Chinese government fails to sever its financial connections with Sudan or to leverage its connections to hold Sudan accountable for ending the genocide in Darfur before December 31,
	 2007.
MatterBodyName:
Committee on Cultural Affairs,
	 Libraries and International Intergroup Relations

MatterName: Denouncing the use by President Bush and Homeland Security Secretary Chertoff of a flawed risk-based allotment of anti-terrorism grants.
MatterTitle:
Resolution denouncing the use by President Bush and Homeland Security Secretary Chertoff of a flawed risk-based allotment of anti-terrorism grants and failing to recognize that New York City is one of the top targets for an international terrorist attack,
	 and calling on President Bush and Homeland Security Secretary Chertoff to increase homeland security funding for New York City.
